## Limitations

The analysis is based on existing studies and expert opinions, which may not account for unforeseen technological advancements or political changes. Additionally, the feasibility of a 100% renewable energy system varies significantly by region, depending on local resources and infrastructure. The economic and social impacts of such a transition are complex and require further investigation.